---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Integrating Payment Solutions | Store">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <img 
      src="/images/blog/payment-blog.jpg" 
      alt="Payment Integration"
      class="w-full aspect-[16/9] object-cover rounded-2xl mb-8"
    />

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <time>November 28, 2023</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 bg-gray-300 rounded-full"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">The Complete Guide to Payment Integration</h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Modern e-commerce demands seamless payment experiences. Here's how to integrate popular payment solutions while maintaining security and user experience.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 my-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Quick Takeaways</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              Multiple payment gateway support
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              PCI compliance considerations
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/>
              </svg>
              Mobile payment optimization
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Understanding Payment Integration</h2>
        <p>
          Modern e-commerce platforms require robust payment processing capabilities. This guide explores implementing secure payment solutions while maintaining a seamless user experience. We'll cover everything from basic setup to advanced features.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Key Implementation Steps</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">Security First</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Implement SSL certificates, data encryption, and secure payment token handling for maximum protection.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">User Experience</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Design intuitive checkout flows with clear error handling and payment confirmation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Looking Ahead</h2>
        <p>
          The future of e-commerce payments lies in adaptability. Stay ready for emerging payment methods and evolving security standards while maintaining a focus on user experience.
        </p>

        <div class="border-t border-gray-200 mt-12 pt-8">
          <a 
            href="/blog" 
            class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 hover:text-black"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
            </svg>
            Back to Blog
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
</style>
